{{cpp/string/char_traits/title|eof}}
{{cpp/string/char_traits/navbar}}
{{ddcl|notes={{mark constexpr since c++11}}&lt;br&gt;{{mark noexcept since c++11}}|
static int_type eof();
}}

Returns a value not equivalent to any valid value of type {{tt|char_type}}.

See {{named req|CharTraits}} for the general requirements on character traits for {{tt|X::eof}}.

===Parameters===
(none)

|{{c|WEOF}}
|-
|{{c/core|char8_t}}
|an implementation-defined constant that&lt;br&gt;cannot appear as a valid UTF-8 code unit
|-
|{{c/core|char16_t}}
|an implementation-defined constant that&lt;br&gt;cannot appear as a valid UTF-16 code unit
|-
|{{c/core|char32_t}}
|an implementation-defined constant that&lt;br&gt;cannot appear as a Unicode code point
|}

Constant.
